data.name: _txtSearchText.ToolTip
data.value:
<Search Term> if needed for your SQL / EA Model Search:
With enter you can run your Search.
Enter your <Search Term> to further specify your search.
If you use hoTools SQL the following wild cards are supported and converted according to your database: - #WC# EA wild card (works also in hoToolsQuery like '*' or '%' - % or * (no or any amount of arbitrary characters, transformed to the used database) - ? or _ (single character, transformed to the used database) - ! or ^ (shortcut for XOR)
e.g.: 'myString*' Everything starting with 'myString' (db independent)
hoTools supports: - EA Searches - SQL searches stored in files with advanced features - LINQ queries for complex searches (LINQPad needed)
